<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>Avil Page (dreamland)</title><link>http://www.avilpage.com</link><description></description><atom:link rel="self" href="http://www.avilpage.com/categories/dreamland.xml" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 03 Aug 2016 13:28:46 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>https://getnikola.com/</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>[Zen Story] In Dreamland!</title><link>http://www.avilpage.com/2014/11/zen-story-in-dreamland/</link><dc:creator>Chillar Anand</dc:creator><description>&lt;div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on"&gt;"Our schoolmaster used to take a nap every afternoon," related a disciple of Soyen Shaku.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We children asked him why he did it and he told us: 'I go to dreamland to meet the old sages just as Confucius did.'&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;When Confucius slept, he would dream of ancient sages and later tell his followers about them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It was extremely hot one day so some of us took a nap. Our schoolmaster scolded us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;'We went to dreamland to meet the ancient sages the same as Confucius did,' we explained.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;'What was the message from those sages?' our schoolmaster demanded.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;One of us replied: 'We went to dreamland and met the sages and asked them if our schoolmaster came there every afternoon, but they said they had never seen any such fellow.'&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; color: #666666; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', Trebuchet, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 20.1599979400635px;"&gt;========================================================================&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style="background-color: white; color: #666666; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', Trebuchet, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 20.1599979400635px;"&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; color: #666666; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', Trebuchet, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 20.1599979400635px;"&gt;Source:Â &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.101zenstories.com/" style="background-color: white; color: #5421bb; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', Trebuchet, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 20.1599979400635px; text-decoration: none;" target="_blank"&gt;101 Zen Stories&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br style="background-color: white; color: #666666; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', Trebuchet, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 20.1599979400635px;"&gt;&lt;br style="background-color: white; color: #666666; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', Trebuchet, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 20.1599979400635px;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.avilpage.com/search/label/zen" style="background-color: white; color: #5421bb; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', Trebuchet, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 20.1599979400635px; text-decoration: none;"&gt;More Zen Stories&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>amazing zen stories</category><category>best short zen stories</category><category>confucius</category><category>dreamland</category><category>zen</category><guid>http://www.avilpage.com/2014/11/zen-story-in-dreamland/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 20 Nov 2014 21:29:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>